Thaere wrote:<BR>
<DIV>BIg loophoole in Raid only AAs: You create a group of five then raid invite your 6th person. The raid leader then moves the 6th person into the primary group. The raid still exists, but its only one group.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR><BR><BR>But by doing that you don't get the Group XP bonus, so you have to decide. Is having access to the raid leadership abilities worth halving your XP gain?<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>I have never noticed a&nbsp; huge difference.&nbsp; example you go to RSS with two groups to take out chalik, you do this and one group stays behind to XP..they are still in the raid but XP is not affected so severely that people notice.<BR>
