<BLOCKQUOTE>Saroc_Luclin wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV></DIV><BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>Just as an addendum.<BR><BR>The main concern the Dev's have with increasing the In-Battle regen rates too much is the risk it will throw off balancing for existing encounters. Health, unlike Mana/End, other than giving the healer heart attacks (and unless you are the MA), makes little difference whether you are at 30Health or Full Health. So having a DPS sit out a battle to regen health faster is not really a good tactic.<BR><BR>But with Mana, you start getting returns much faster when you start playing with the regen rates in a non-trivial fashion. A caster who's OOM and a caster who has 20M have a world of difference in what they have available to them. (I may not be saying this clearly).<BR><BR>Lets take a cleric who is completely OOM, and who has a regen rate of 80 mana per tick while sitting. (And ignore all other factors like focii).<BR><BR>Under the current system, in order to gain 400 mana, enough to cast CH, it would take this cleric 30 seconds to regen enough mana to cast again.<BR><BR>Now, lets consider a system where your mana regen doubles every tick you are sitting.<BR>At 6 seconds, the cleric has 80 mana. <BR>At 12 seconds, the cleric has 240 mana.<BR>At 18 seconds, the cleric has 560 mana, more than enough for CH. CH is now castable in 2/3rds the time than before, and the CLR ends up with 160 mana to spare (not counting Focus effects).<BR>(Or you can keep sitting and get:<BR>At 24 seconds, the cleric has 1200 mana (3+ CH's)<BR>At 30 seconds, the cleric has 2480 mana.<BR>At 36 seconds, the cleric has 5040 mana, and is probably 50M or so by now.<BR>(This is an extreme; such a rate would probably be too much)<BR><BR>Or lets consider a system where you get your original regen rate again for every tick.<BR>At 6 seconds, you have 80mana<BR>At 12 seconds you have 240mana<BR>At 18 seconds you have 480mana, and are ready to CH again.<BR>At 24 seconds you have 800mana<BR>At 30 secodns you have 1200mana <BR>At 36 seconds you have 1680mana<BR>At 42 seconds you have 2240 mana and at 20-30M roughly<BR>At 48 seconds you have 2880 mana<BR>At 54 seconds you have 3600 mana<BR>At 1 minute, you have 4400 mana, and approaching 40-50M. <BR><BR>A more reasonable rate, but probably still too fast for in battle regen, since if you can stay seated for 30 seconds during the fight, a cleric could get 3 CHeals worth of mana (Probably 4+ CHeals given Focus effects, AA's, and standing/mount regen while casting considerations) Many clerics would be nearly full mana after 90 seconds or so.<BR><BR>Even if you double the period between rate increases, you're still looking at 2 CH's in 30-36 seconds, and 3-4 CH's in 42 seconds.<BR><BR>The challenge would be to find an increasing regen rate formula that works for most/all levels of all classes which does not also destablize existing encounters for those at the appropriate levels to handle them. <BR><BR>Consider for example, General Reparm in PoFire (I think I got his name right) with a level/AA/gear appropriate raid. His difficulty would be diminished if the first wave of healers and nukers could be back in for the final stages of the fight with suitable mana pools because they were able to med that fast enough out of range of his drain.<BR><BR>So instead of taking up that particular challenge (and the balancing issues it could cause for future expansions), the Dev's seem to prefer to try and find a different solution, like trying to add in a "In-Battle State" to the game, or maybe some other solution they haven't breathed a word of. (For all we know they are trying to come up with a suitable mana/end regen formula but haven't hinted at it to keep speculation low)<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>that is not how the increased HP regen by sitting works.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; you would have to sit for about 5 ticks for every increase in hp regen you have.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>IE If you sit down for hp regen your hp regen per tick goes like this</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>45</DIV>
<DIV>45</DIV>
<DIV>45</DIV>
<DIV>45</DIV>
<DIV>45</DIV>
<DIV>56</DIV>
<DIV>56</DIV>
<DIV>56</DIV>
<DIV>56</DIV>
<DIV>56</DIV>
<DIV>56</DIV>
<DIV>67</DIV>
<DIV>67</DIV>
<DIV>67</DIV>
<DIV>67</DIV>
<DIV>67</DIV>
<DIV>67</DIV>
<DIV>78</DIV>
<DIV>78</DIV>
<DIV>78</DIV>
<DIV>78</DIV>
<DIV>etc</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You get the point--and of course that a higher level would have higher hp regen but same percentage increase.&nbsp;&nbsp; so with caster mana it would be</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>45</DIV>
<DIV>45</DIV>
