		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Huron-EMU wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Consider divine resurrection as well. 5aa every 24hrs will give 100% mana. and yes you can use it after you been rezzed, just loot your gear first, then pop it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Nearing 10k mana myself, I find mana regen to be just fine after a wipe. Yes it takes&nbsp;a few minutes, but the clerics are rezzed first (if raid), if only to get their clicky out and start rezzing others.&nbsp; If I was fm 5min after I buffed after a wipe, the guild wouldnt be. They rethink strats etc.&nbsp; 10 to 15min after clerics are rezzed back into a raid wipe zone, we're back in action.&nbsp; Nothing wrong, move along.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Aye I learned that trick some time ago.&nbsp; You do not get the 100% XP restored if you do a 96% first, but you loot everything but one backpack and you then div rez, rez effects are gone and you get 100% of your hp and mana restored.</P>
<P>The problem I have with using that ability after a raid wipe is that you are going to have to wait for the rest of the raid to med anyway, so there is little point in div rezzing yourself IMO.&nbsp; I usually save div rez for when I die in the middle of an event and I need to get back into healing ASAP, so I get rezzed, I loot then I div rez myself.</P>	
